==Turkish==
===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|tr|[jɛˈmɛc]}}
* {{hyphenation|tr|ye|mek}}
===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|tr|ota|یمك|tr=yemek|gloss=to eat, consume}}, from {{inh|tr|trk-pro|*yē-||to eat}}.<ref>{{R:tut-pro:SDM|*jē-|url=http://starling.rinet.ru/cgi-bin/response.cgi?single=1&basename=%2fdata%2falt%2fturcet&text_number=++25&root=config}}</ref>
{{rel-top|cognates}}
Cognate with {{cog|otk|𐰘𐰃𐰘𐰇|tr=yéyü|t=eating}}, {{cog|oui||tr=ye-||to eat}}, {{cog|xqa||tr=yḗmēk||to eat, destroy}}, {{cog|az|yemək||to eat}}, {{cog|cv|ҫиме||to eat}}, {{cog|kk|жеу||to eat}}, {{cog|kjh|чирге||to eat}}, {{cog|ky|жөө||to eat}}, {{cog|alt|јиир||to eat}}, {{cog|tk|iýmek||to eat}}, {{cog|tyv|чиир||to eat}}, {{cog|ug|يىمەك||to eat}}, {{cog|uz|yemoq||to eat}}, {{cog|sah|сиэ||to eat}}.
{{rel-bottom}}
====Verb====
{{tr-verb|yer}}
# {{lb|tr|transitive}} to [[eat]]
#: {{ux|tr|Her gün iki öğün haşlanmış patates '''yemekten''' bıktım.|I'm tired of '''eating''' boiled potatoes twice every day.}}
# {{lb|tr|transitive}} to [[require]], [[use up]], [[consume]]
# {{lb|tr|transitive|of an insect}} to [[bite]], [[eat]] someone up
# {{lb|tr|transitive}} to [[drain]], [[wear]] someone down, take a lot out of someone
# {{lb|tr|transitive|slang}} to [[kill]]
# {{lb|tr|transitive|slang}} to [[lay]], [[have sex]] with, [[kiss]], [[lick]], [[suck]]
# {{lb|tr|transitive}} to [[capture]] (as in [[chess]])
#: {{ux|tr|Piyon düz ve ileri doğru hareket etse de karşı oyuncunun taşlarını çapraz olarak '''yer'''.|Even though the pawn moves straight and forward, it '''captures''' the opponent pieces diagonally.}}
# {{lb|tr|transitive}} to [[break]] (usually a [[low-cost]] household item)
#: {{ux|tr|Kumandayı '''yemişsiniz''' yine.|So you '''broke''' the TV remote again.}}
